"TC-SRCH-0021","Find Patient Record / Search","Security - Injection","SQL injection payload in search box does not execute or leak data","Security","System","P1","Critical","High","Logged in as Clinician; on Find Patient Record screen; DB audit logging enabled","1. Open Find Patient Record | 2. Enter a SQL injection payload | 3. Submit search | 4. Observe results and server logs","Query=' OR '1'='1","No patients are returned beyond legitimate matches; query is parameterized; no SQL error or full-table dump; payload logged safely","Partially-Automatable","REQ-SRCH-009","Security; PHI/Privacy; Audit","OpenMRS"
"TC-SRCH-0022","Find Patient Record / Search","Security - Injection","XSS payload in search box is neutralized in results rendering","Security","System","P1","Critical","High","Logged in as Clinician; on Find Patient Record screen","1. Open Find Patient Record | 2. Enter a script-tag payload | 3. Submit search | 4. Inspect rendered DOM","Query=<script>alert('x')</script>","Payload is HTML-escaped and not executed; no alert dialog; results region shows no-match safely","Partially-Automatable","REQ-SRCH-009","Security; PHI/Privacy","OpenMRS"
"TC-SRCH-0023","Find Patient Record / Search","Security - Authorization","Unauthenticated user cannot access the patient search endpoint","Security","Integration","P1","Critical","High","No active session; search REST endpoint URL known","1. Clear session/cookies | 2. Call the patient search endpoint directly | 3. Observe HTTP response","GET /openmrs/ws/rest/v1/patient?q=Test (no auth)","Server returns 401 Unauthorized (or redirect to login); no patient data is returned","Automatable","REQ-SRCH-010","Security; PHI/Privacy; Regulatory/Compliance","OpenMRS"
"TC-SRCH-0024","Find Patient Record / Search","Security - Authorization","User without Get Patients privilege is denied search results","Security","Integration","P1","Critical","High","Logged in as a role lacking the ""Get Patients"" privilege; on the app","1. Authenticate as the restricted role | 2. Attempt patient search via UI or API | 3. Observe response","Role=NoPatientAccess; Query=Test","Access is denied with 403/authorization error; no patient records returned","Partially-Automatable","REQ-SRCH-010","Security; PHI/Privacy; Regulatory/Compliance","OpenMRS"
"TC-SRCH-0025","Find Patient Record / Search","Audit","Patient search access is recorded in the audit log","Security","Integration","P1","High","High","Logged in as Clinician; audit/logging module enabled; on Find Patient Record screen","1. Perform a patient search | 2. Open a matched patient record | 3. Inspect the audit log","Query=John Tester; User=clinician1","An audit entry records the user, timestamp, and the patient record accessed, satisfying HIPAA access-tracking","Partially-Automatable","REQ-SRCH-011","Audit; PHI/Privacy; Regulatory/Compliance","OpenMRS"
"TC-SRCH-0026","Find Patient Record / Search","Pagination","Result set exceeding page size renders pagination controls","Functional","Regression","P2","Medium","Medium","Logged in as Clinician; at least 60 patients share family name ""Common""; default page size 10; on Find Patient Record screen","1. Search for the shared family name | 2. Observe results table | 3. Verify pagination controls present","Query=Common; ~60 matches; pageSize=10","Results are paginated; page controls (next/previous or load-more) are shown and first page lists page-size rows","Automatable","REQ-SRCH-012","Patient Safety; Usability","OpenMRS"
