"TC-SRCH-0035","Find Patient Record / Search","Performance","Search response renders within acceptable time under typical load","Functional","System","P1","High","High","Logged in as Clinician; database has 100k+ patients; on Find Patient Record screen","1. Enter a common family name | 2. Measure time from submit to first results render | 3. Repeat 5 times","Query=Smith; DB size=100k+","First page of results renders within 2 seconds for the 95th percentile; UI shows loading indicator while pending","Partially-Automatable","REQ-SRCH-016","Patient Safety; Performance","OpenMRS"
"TC-SRCH-0036","Find Patient Record / Search","Performance","Loading indicator is displayed during search latency","Usability","Regression","P3","Low","Low","Logged in as Clinician; network throttled to simulate latency; on Find Patient Record screen","1. Enter a search term | 2. Observe UI while request is in flight","Query=Smith; throttled network","A spinner or progress indicator is shown while results load and is removed when results arrive","Partially-Automatable","REQ-SRCH-016","Usability","OpenMRS"
"TC-SRCH-0037","Find Patient Record / Search","Decision Table","Name vs identifier vs no-match matrix yields correct branch","Decision Table","Regression","P2","High","Medium","Logged in as Clinician; patient John Tester (id 10010X) exists; on Find Patient Record screen","1. Enter a valid name -> verify name branch | 2. Enter a valid identifier -> verify id branch | 3. Enter an unmatched value -> verify empty branch","Cases: ""John Tester""=name-match; ""10010X""=id-match; ""Zzqx""=no-match","Each input class routes to the correct outcome: name match list, exact identifier match, and empty-state respectively","Partially-Automatable","REQ-SRCH-017","Patient Safety; Data Integrity","OpenMRS"
